This simple plugin gives you quick access to the Palette.fm photo colorization system created by Emil Wallner
PS. Button Download - at the bottom of the frame, if necessary, increase the size of the PP plugin panel ;)

Generates color palettes from the visible Photopea document using k-means clustering (frequency), luminance sorting (brightness), HSL saturation ranking (chroma), and hue binning with averaging (hue). Transparent pixels are ignored; each palette can be exported back to Photopea as a new document.

Insert a grid layer into the current document or open a new document with a grid. 
Configurable:
* Horizontal / vertical step (px)
* Independent angles (0.1° precision) for each family of lines
* Line thickness (px)
* Line color
* Optional crisp 1px alignment (0.5px offset)
* Optional border margin (skip drawing near edges)
P.S. Works in Vectorpea

Guilloché for Photopea is a plugin that opens Guilloché Lab generator in a new browser tab and lets you send results back into Photopea/Vectorpea as a new document. 
The plugin page runs inside Photopea as an iframe. When you click Open generator, it launches the generator with a unique sessionId. After designing, the generator’s top-right actions Export PNG/SVG to Photopea return the image to the plugin for inserting into Photopea/Vectorpea docs.

The generator implements a broad palette of parametric methods used in generative art: Polar Harmonics; Trochoid/Spiro; Lissajous; Harmonograph; Rhodonea (Rose) and Rose Mix; Maurer Rose; Superformula; Superellipse (Lamé); Fourier Epicycles; Logarithmic Spiral; Cycloidal Stars; Phyllotaxis; and Clothoid/Euler spiral. Each method exposes clean controls (amplitudes, frequencies, phases, etc.) with live canvas preview, SVG/PNG export, and preset management via JSON.
P.S. Works in Vectorpea

Distort Lab for Photopea covers a wide range of geometric warps—from familiar creative tools to сonformal maps and analytic experiments.

Workflow niceties: import/export per-filter presets, baking intermediate results, and round-trip export back to Photopea as a new document or via the clipboard in new layer.

Real-time parameter changes can help explore smooth, artifact-free deformations in real time for design.

F1_vs_F2 for Photopea is a generative art playground that plots two expressions f1(x,y) and f2(x,y) over a 2D domain to create dense point-cloud visuals. You get a fast expression parser, seeded randomness, multiple sampling modes (grid with on-line / between-line phases, or random), and several projections (Rectilinear, Polar, Aitoff, Hammer, Lambert, Mollweide) with rotation, marker style, size, and alpha controls. The principles are very similar to the approach used Python library Samina.

Type your formulas, pick the sampling window and projection, and the renderer evaluates hundreds of thousands of points, auto-fits them to a square canvas, and shows timing and point counts in the status badge. Safe built-ins include many functions and random parameters p1..p8 (see help), so you can prototype quickly while keeping results stable via seeds. The lab has a link to an archive with many presets for a first acquaintance with the functionality.

Save/load full presets as JSON, download PNG locally, or click Export PNG to Photopea to create a new document in Photopea (when opened from the plugin panel; a sessionId in the URL is handled automatically).
P.S. Works in Vectorpea.

PLAKÁT SZERKESZTÉSE
0. Szabadon használható, kizárólag az utcanév átírásával, más módosítást ne végezz rajta! Ne rakj rá semmit! Köszönöm!
1. Kattints kétszer a plakát szövegére, írd át az utcád nevét, használj nagybetűt.
2. Mentéshez: File > Export as > PDF (rasterize all és a vectorize text legyen kipipálva) > SAVE
3. A plakát mérete 20x20 cm 80 g-os papírra elég nyomtatni.
4. A vágásnál figyelj, hogy a fotó készítőjének a neve, Valuska Gábor a képen maradjon.


PLAKÁT KIRAGASZTÁSA
0. Plakátozás előtt olvass Krasznahorkait.
1. Tiszteld a várost és a környezeted! Csak olyan helyre ragassz, ahol már korábban is voltak hasonló plakátok.
1. Használj kültérre alkalmas tapétaragasztót, festékboltokban segítenek kiválasztani a megfelelőt.
2. Célszerű egy befőttesüvegbe megkeverni a ragasztót, abban a legkönnyebb szállítani.
3. A ragasztás menete: 1. Kend le a felületet 2. Kend le a plakát hátulját. 3. Helyezd fel. 4. Kend le a plakát elejét is, a szélekre figyelj.
4. Plakátozás után is olvass Krasznahorkait.
